<li id="cite_note-16"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFSchulman1971">Schulman, Arnold (1971). <i>Baba</i>. <a href="/wiki/Viking_Press" title="Viking Press">Viking Press</a>. pp.&#160;122–124. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/067014343X" class="internal">ISBN 0-670-14343-X</a>.  "One of Baba's two sisters, however, who claims to have been present at his birth, says that the cobra was not found under the blanket, but several hours after Baba was born a cobra was seen outside the house, a sight not uncommon in the village."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Baba&amp;rft.aulast=Schulman&amp;rft.aufirst=Arnold&amp;rft.au=Schulman%2C+Arnold&amp;rft.date=1971&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B122%E2%80%93124&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BViking+Press%5D%5D&amp;rft.isbn=0-670-14343-X&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Sathya_Sai_Baba"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
